HEADWORD: full-length
<hw>full-length</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>accommodating the
full height of the human figure; <as>as, a <ex>full-length</ex>
mirror</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>representing the full height of the human figure;
<as>as, a <ex>full-length</ex> portrait</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>unabridged; <as>as, the <ex>full-length</ex>
play</as>. Opposite of <ant>abridged</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> complete, uncut.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Full-manned</ent>⟦br⟧
